The catholic or patriarch of the Armenians resides in the monastery of Ekmiafin, three leagues from Erivan. Forty-seven archbissiops, each of whom may claim the obedience of four or five suffragans, are consecrated by his hand 3 but the far greater part are only titular prelates, who dignify with their presence and service the simplicity of his court.
